The paper deals with long-term protection of sensitive digital information, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The focus is on protecting large datasets consisting of relatively small data items, which suggests a connection to database systems (cs.DB). The use of renewable timestamps and secret sharing also suggests a connection to cryptography (cs.CY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient solution for protecting and verifying large datasets, which suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
